12456789
```

As a recommendation, if you plan on using _continue_, consider using the _[iterative for-loop](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/for.html)_.  
Having _i_ increment at one location can prove helpful as you build your _loop_ code.

You could, also, use a _[do-while](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/while.html)_ loop, and increment _i_ during the conditional statement.

```java
int i = 1;
do {
    if (i == 3) continue;
    System.out.print(i);
} while (++i &lt;= 9);
```

