Find text is not yet available for Google Sheet API. Please star this [issue tracker FR][1] to get notified on any updates. 

A workaround based on this SO [answer][2], &quot;You can get the data for the range you are searching on, and then iterate over it looking for a match. &quot;
Here is his code snippet:

    /**
    * Finds a value within a given range. 
    * @param value The value to find.
    * @param range The range to search in.
    * @return A range pointing to the first cell containing the value, 
    * or null if not found.
    */
    function find(value, range) {
    var data = range.getValues();
    for (var i = 0; i &lt; data.length; i++) {
    for (var j = 0; j &lt; data[i].length; j++) {
    if (data[i][j] == value) {
    return range.getCell(i + 1, j + 1);
    }
    }
    }
    return null;
    }

*NOTE*: Code sample is in google-apps-script

Like in this code snippet, you will need to set the range first, then check if value will match inside the range.


